  "informal_statement": "Partitioning a finite set by a predicate (here, evenness) and its negation always accounts for every element exactly once: the two filtered cardinalities sum to the whole set's cardinality.",
  "informal_proof_idea": "Directly `Finset.card_filter_add_card_filter_not`, whose sole explicit argument is the predicate — the underlying `Finset` is inferred from the goal.",
  "formal_statement_pp": "theorem card_filter_partition (s : Finset ℕ) : (s.filter (fun a => a % 2 = 0)).card + (s.filter (fun a => ¬ (a % 2 = 0))).card = s.card",
